From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 15:05:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L46: general libjvm.so-data capability table (data trampoline)

The recurring class-2 problem — generated codecache code can't address a
libjvm.so .data/.bss global (mov gives tag-0; PCC-relative adrp is out of
range; DDC is null) — now has a GENERAL solution instead of per-table
Thread fields.

Verified first (docs/37) that no single segment-wide .data cap exists:
&global caps are tightly bounded (subobject bounds on), the edata/end
linker markers are zero-length, DDC is null, and CHERI can't widen.

Solution (data analogue of the call trampoline): at CODEGEN time, where
`&global` IS a valid C++ capability, register it in cap_data_table
(cap_data_id_for, deduped, pre-sized to 1024 so the backing array never
moves) and get a 1-based id. Thread::_cap_data_base is seeded with a cap
to the table's backing array (in Thread ctor + re-seeded for the main
thread in init_globals, like _cap_dispatch). New helper
MacroAssembler::lea_libjvm_global(dst, global) emits:
    ldr dst, [rthread, #cap_data_base_offset]   ; &table[0]
    ldr dst, [dst, #(id-1)*16]                  ; table[id-1] = &global (valid cap)
Then the site accesses the global through dst. Scales to any number of
globals; the cap always comes straight from C++ with correct bounds.

First use — L46 invoke return entry table in prepare_invoke. Fixed all
three issues at once: (1) reach the .data global via lea_libjvm_global,
(2) ×16 stride (not ×8) for the 16-byte cap entries, (3) cap-LDR the
entry so lr is a valid return capability.

RESULT: the invoke-return-entry load works (lr = a valid codecache
continuation cap). Execution advances into the actual method dispatch.
Next fault (L47): an implicit null check `ldr xzr, [receiver]` with a
null receiver — needs the SIGPROT handler to perform implicit-null-check
→ NullPointerException dispatch (the SafeFetch-style mechanism), or the
receiver computation is off (to determine next).

New files: cap_data_table_aarch64.cpp.

Session: 46 commits, 110 build iterations, L25-L46 resolved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

